 References [68], [90] assert that

•surface migration is still dominant in 10 \$\mu\$ m wide polycrystalline Cu lines for \$T < 250\$ °C;
•drift rate increased as line width decreased, which is consistent with the fact that less material needs to be removed for a narrower line to cause EM damage;
•the observed lifetime dependence on interconnect cross-sectional area favors an interfacial diffusion mechanism, which is also observed in the work by [92].

